item_description: To analyze the spectral power in sleep stages, periods, cycles, hours according to your needs.

steps.name: PSA
steps.description: How to define the PSA, how is performed and how to use the output.

steps.name: Input Files
steps.description:
Manage the PSG files you want to perform the PSA on.

The PSG file and the accessory file must be in the same folder.

Open your files
 (edf) : tsv file is optional
 (eeg) : NATUS subject folder is mandatory
 (sts) : sig file is mandatory

Select the montage and channels

steps.name: Events to exclude
steps.description:
Select events to exclude from the PSA (i.e. artifacts).

Start by selecting one PSG or multiple files (with the ctrl key pressed), then select an event group or name.

Be aware that the files must still be highlighted in the GUI to apply the 'Select All' option.

steps.name: Filter Settings
steps.description: Define the EEG filtering of your study.

steps.name: Section Selection
steps.description: Select the sections i.e. events, sleep stage and/or period to perform the PSA on.

steps.name: Annotations Selection
steps.description:
Select the annotations to perform the PSA on.

Start by selecting one PSG or multiple files (with the ctrl key pressed), then select an event group or name.

Be aware that the files must still be highlighted in the GUI to apply the 'Select All' option.

steps.name: Spectral Settings
steps.description: Define the spectral settings of the PSA for your study

steps.name: Output Files
steps.description: Define the PSA output files for your study.

list.name: Hours and Cycles
list.description: Define the maximum number of hours and cycles to report.

{'defined_option': 'Aeschbach 1993', 'Include_SOREMP': '1', 'Include_last_incompl': '1', 'Include_all_incompl': '1', 'dur_ends_REMP': '15', 'NREM_min_len_first': '15.0', 'NREM_min_len_mid_last': '15.0', 'NREM_min_len_val_last': '5.0', 'REM_min_len_first': '0.5', 'REM_min_len_mid': '5', 'REM_min_len_last': '0.5', 'mv_end_REMP': '1', 'sleep_stages': 'N2, N3, N4, R', 'details': '

Adjust options based on [1].

\xa0

NREM-REMS cycles were defined [...] by the succession of a NREMS episode of at least 15 min duration and a REMS episode of at least 5 min duration. No minimal duration of the REMS episode was required for the completion of the first and last cycle. NREMS episodes were defined as the time interval between the first occurrence of stage 2 and the first occurrence of REMS within a cycle. Consequently REMS episodes were defined as the time intervals between two consecutive NREMS episodes or the time interval between the last NREMS episode and the final awakening. Thus occasional stage 1 epochs between REMS and stage 2 were included in the REMS episode. The reasons for selecting this criterion were the similarity of the EEG in REMS and stage 1, the better delimitation of cycle onset by using stage 2 instead of stage 1, and the fact that the initiation of cycle 1 with stage 2 corresponds to a frequently used criterion of sleep onset.

\xa0

[1] Aeschbach D, Borbely AA. All-night dynamics of the human sleep EEG. J Sleep Res. 1993 Jun; 2(2):70-81. https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2869.1993.tb00065.x

'}
